# VM inventory for Vm-watchdog
# Copy to vms.conf and fill in your values. vms.conf is gitignored.
#
# Format: name:ip:ssh_user:extra_ufw_ports
#   name           — short hostname used for monitoring labels and logs
#   ip             — SSH-reachable IP address
#   ssh_user       — SSH username (must have sudo access)
#   extra_ufw_ports — comma-separated ports to open publicly (e.g. 80/tcp,443/tcp)
#                    leave empty for SSH-only VMs
#
# Lines starting with # are ignored.

# Examples:
# proxy:192.168.1.10:admin:80/tcp,81/tcp,443/tcp
# mediaserver:192.168.1.11:ubuntu:
# vpn:192.168.1.12:vpn:51820/udp
# homelab:192.168.1.13:user:8080/tcp
